sam2matrix - This program outputs for each read the ids of references it.
=========================================================================

SYNOPSIS
    sam2Matrix -sf SAMFILE -rf READSFILE -gf GENOMEFILE-o OUTFILE

DESCRIPTION
    This program determines for each read in the reference file if it has an entry in the provided sam files stating
    that it mapped. Afterwards a file is generated containing a row for each read which contains the read ID and the
    index of the mapped references.

    -h, --help
          Displays this help message.
    --version
          Display version information
    -sf, --samFiles SAMFILES
          Sam files. Valid filetype is: sam.
    -rf, --referenceFile FILE
          Read name file. Valid filetypes are: fa, fasta, fq, and fastq.
    -gf, --genomeFiles GENOMES
          Names of the references of the corresponding sam file.. Valid filetypes are: fa, fasta, fq, and fastq.
    -o, --outputFile FILE
          Output file. Valid filetype is: csv.

EXAMPLES
    sam2Gasic -sf sam.sam -rf reads.fa -gf ecoli.fa -o out.csv
          Call with SAMFILE set to "sam.sam", with READSFILE set to "reads.fa", with GENOMEFILE set to "ecoli.fa" and
          OUTFILE set to "out.csv", where "ecoli.fa" is the file used as reference to generate "sam.sam"

VERSION
    sam2Matrix version: 0.1
    Last update April 2014
